'''Australian Wormy Chestnut''' or '''Firestreak''' is a common name for [[lumber]] of [[Eucalyptus obliqua]], [[Eucalyptus sieberi]] and [[Eucalyptus fastigata]] grown in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], southern [[New South Wales]], and [[Tasmania]] in [[Australia]]. It is a [[hardwood]] species commonly used in flooring applications.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hardwood Species Names|url=http://insightflooring.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/34_Hardwood-Species-Names-1.pdf|website=insightflooring.com.au|publisher=Australian Timber Flooring Association|accessdate=6 July 2017|date=Feb 2011}}</ref>
