{{Infobox power transmission line | name = Three Gorges &ndash; Guangdong HVDC Transmission | photo = | caption = | map = | map_caption = | country = China | state = | province = | coordinates = {{Coord|30|27|26|N|112|08|18|E|type:landmark|name=Three Gorges-Guangdong Transmission - Jingzhou Static Inverter Plant}} &ndash; {{Coord|23|16|15|N|114|12|5|E|type:landmark|name=Three Gorges-Guangdong Transmission - Huizhou Static Inverter Plant}} | lat = | long = | direction = South-southeast | start = Jingzhou, [[Three Gorges Dam]] | through = | finish = Huizhou, Guangdong | par = | owner = | partners = | operator = | cable_manufacturer= | cable_installer= | cable_layer = | substation_manufacturer=[[ABB Group]] | substation_installer= | contractors = | construction= | expected = | est = May 27, 2004 | decom = | type = overhead transmission line | current_type=HVDC | length_km = 940 | capacity = 3000 MW | AC_voltage = | DC_voltage = ±500 kV | poles_no = 2 | circuits_no = }} {{GeoGroupTemplate}} The '''HVDC Three Gorges – Guangdong''' is a 940&nbsp;kilometre-long bipolar [[High-voltage direct current|HVDC]] transmission line in [[China]] for the transmission of electric power from the [[Three Gorges Dam|Three Gorges]] power plant to the area of [[Guangdong]]. The powerline went into service in 2004. It runs from the static inverter station Jingzhou near the Three Gorges power plant to the static inverter plant Huizhou near Guangdong. The HVDC Three Gorges-Guangdong is a [[Bipolar electricity transmission|bipolar]] 500&nbsp;[[Volt|kV]] powerline with a maximum transmission power rating of 3,000&nbsp;[[megawatt]]s.<ref name="ABB">{{cite web|url=http://www.abb.com/industries/ap/db0003db004333/38fb68a9904075dbc125774900475a15.aspx|title=Three Gorges - Guangdong HVDC Transmission|accessdate=2012-10-10|author=ABB}}</ref>
