The following is a list of [[Hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] [[power station]]s in [[Brazil]] with a [[nameplate capacity]] of at least 100 MW.
{{Expand list|date=October 2016}}

According to the ''Associação Brasileira de Distribuidores de Energia Elétrica'' (ABRADEE) there are 201 hydroelectric power stations in Brazil with a nameplate capacity of more than 30 MW; the total capacity of these power stations in 2015 was 84,703 MW. There are an additional 476 hydroelectric power stations with a nameplate capacity between 1 and 30 MW and 496 micro hydroelectric power stations with a nameplate capacity of less than 1 MW.<ref name="ab"/>

